{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, since the mean of φ was zero, the student and item parameters were less biased, with φ included in SAD-IRT.",
    "Given the high similarities between the item-response parameter estimations of SAD-IRT and the base models, SAD-IRT can interpret the estimated IRT parameters, such as the student ability parameter θ and the item difficulty parameter β, in the same way as IRT.",
    "The relationship between emotion and student performance, similar to the φ-emotion relationship, is also complex due to the diverse emotions present in the learning domain (Pekrun, 2011; Fenza et al., 2017).",
    "Furthermore, we had to consider the tradeoff between predictive performance and model interpretability (Rudin, 2019).",
    "Given these factors, we found establishing a clear relationship challenging."
  ]
}